# Implementation Plan - Pastel Layout Visualizer Chrome Extension

Create a Chrome V3 Extension tailored for frontend designers and developers. It will automatically apply beautiful pastel/light colors to HTML elements to make layout visualization easy. It also includes an interactive "Inspect & Color" mode to hover over elements and color only that element and its descendants.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The extension will run locally as a Chrome Extension. To install it, you will need to load it as an "Unpacked Extension" via `chrome://extensions/` in Developer Mode. We will provide detailed verification instructions.
>
> **Design Highlights**:
> - **Premium Glassmorphic Popup UI**: Sleek dark/light theme, modern typography (Inter), rounded controls, subtle animations.
> - **Pastel Color Generation**: Uses HSL color space with controlled saturation (60-80%) and lightness (85-95%) to guarantee colors are soft, light, and pastel.
> - **Original State Retention**: The original inline styles of elements will be saved in `data-` attributes so turning off the visualizer restores the page's original look perfectly.

---

## Proposed Architecture & Files

The project will consist of the following files:
1. `manifest.json` - Chrome V3 extension configuration.
2. `popup.html` - Premium UI popup controls.
3. `popup.css` - Styling for the popup UI.
4. `popup.js` - Handles user selections in the popup and communicates with the content script.
5. `content.js` - Content script that runs on web pages to apply background colors and handle inspection.
6. `icons/` - Modern icons (16, 48, 128) representing the extension.

