## Proposed Changes

### [Chrome Extension Base]

#### [NEW] [manifest.json](file:///e:/2026/July/Colorr/manifest.json)
Configures the Extension under Manifest V3:
- Permissions: `activeTab`, `storage`, `scripting`.
- Action popup: `popup.html`.
- Content script: `content.js` to run on all pages.

#### [NEW] [popup.html](file:///e:/2026/July/Colorr/popup.html)
A premium interface to control:
- **Toggle All Elements**: Button to color all elements on the page.
- **Inspect & Color**: Button to toggle inspect mode (hover to highlight, click to color target + children).
- **Outline Mode**: Toggle to show/hide outlines (1px solid/dashed pastel) on elements.
- **Pastel Palette Types**: Select box or tabs for different pastel moods (Soft Rainbow, Warm Pastels, Cool Pastels, Monochrome Light).
- **Clear All**: Reset page back to its original styles.

#### [NEW] [popup.css](file:///e:/2026/July/Colorr/popup.css)
Visual design:
- Sleek dark-mode container with blur backdrop (glassmorphism style).
- Modern buttons with hover transitions.
- Interactive toggle switches.
- Gradient highlights.

#### [NEW] [popup.js](file:///e:/2026/July/Colorr/popup.js)
Handles click events and communication:
- Sends messages to the active tab's `content.js`.
- Queries the current tab to see if visualization or inspection is active and updates the popup UI accordingly.
- Persists user preferences using local/sync storage.

#### [NEW] [content.js](file:///e:/2026/July/Colorr/content.js)
Core logic that manipulates the target webpage's DOM:
- **Color All Elements**: Walks the DOM tree and applies pastel colors to backgrounds. Before coloring, saves the element's original background and transition properties in `data-original-bg` and `data-original-transition`.
- **Inspect Mode**:
  - Highlights elements under mouse cursor using a thin, animated pastel overlay or outline.
  - On click, intercepts the event, stops navigation, and applies pastel background colors to the clicked element and all its children recursively.
- **Outlines**: Dynamically appends/removes style rules to display outlines on all colored elements.
- **Clear Settings**: Traverses the DOM to remove colors/outlines and restore saved styles.

